text: We need to urgently make the transition to a green economy. The conservatives pretend this will hurt average people. No! It will hurt these people most if we don’t act! These people can’t escape air pollution in dirty cities by buying a second home!
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him

text: Salaries are too low in Hungary. The people at the top are doing well but ordinary workers are not doing well: teachers, railway workers, factory workers all need a pay rise, with the help of the trade unions.

text:

#ItsTime that companies making big profits in Europe pay fair taxes here.
We need a fair minimum wage in every member state of the European Union.
We need to put an end to the pay gap between women and men.

text:
The silent majority in Europe is too often intimidated by those who shout and spread hate.

We have a responsibility to give them a voice and build the EU which they want, based on our fundamental values.

The EU must work for all citizens. We need an EU for the many not the few. https://t.co/Z4OSRql9CQ
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text:
There is not going to be a European army any time soon.

We need more cooperation in the field of defence but we don’t need this.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text:
If you talk about security, you need to talk about an American President who doesn’t value a strong Europe.

And you have to talk about Russia. We can’t be obsessed but we can’t be naive.

Europe needs to be tough and united if we are to protect our citizens.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: RT @PES_PSE: There is an alternative to the Europe of Orban and Salvini. We are ready to lead that alternative. #ItsTime #FlorenceDebate @T…
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text:
We also need more transparency to maintain the trust of voters in European democracy.

Conservative forces are still refusing to have a mandatory transparency register for EU lobbyists.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We have given the European Parliament and the European people the chance to choose the future of the European Union with the #Spitzenkandidat process. To take that away would be bad for democracy.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text:
If we screw up the ecological transformation then we won’t be able to look our children in the eye.

We can do it, but it needs to be socially sustainable too.

That means that those who can pay more will pay more.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text:
We need to focus our investments on the circular economy.

We need to make the move away from fossil fuels and towards more renewable energy and sustainable industries.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text:
Our middle classes are suffering and shrinking.

We need to fix this by creating responsible fiscal systems.

We need major corporations to pay fair taxes.

And we need to increase wages for the middle classes.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text:
By the end of this month you will have to take a crucial decision about the very soul of Europe.

👉 People in Europe want to go forward not backward

👉 They want equality

👉 They want cooperation 

👉 They want sustainability

✊ We need to be on their side ✊ https://t.co/DSmseYn1j9

text:
Costs of living are getting closer in Eastern and Western Europe. But wages are not keeping up. That’s another reason for trade unions to be given a stronger role to support workers in their negotiations with their employers.
#MaastrichtDebate

text:

And we need strong trade unions for strong workers’ rights.

#MaastrichtDebate

users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him

text: El destino de España, el destino de Europa, ¡están en las muy capacitadas manos de vuestro presidente!

users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Como vuestro presidente el será capaz de diseñar la Europa que queremos y necesitamos: la Europa de los valores que habéis llevado a España y que queremos para el resto del continente.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: En el Consejo Europeo es respetado y valorado por los otros primeros ministros por su capacidad tendiendo puentes y por ser un líder que entiende las necesidades de Europa. En menos de un año él ha devuelto a España a la posición de liderazgo que merece.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Ya sabemos que Pedro es de lejos la mejor persona para liderar España y su ciudadanía hacia un futuro brillante. Pero, ¿os he dicho alguna vez sobre su rol en la Unión Europea?
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text:
Las leyes garantizan nuestros derechos como ciudadanos, y se cambian a través del diálogo para sumar mayorías.

¡Para eso está la política! Para dialogar y como herramienta de cambio.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Como Vicepresidente de la Comisión Europea ya lo he dicho muchas veces, y hoy lo repito como Candidato Socialista a la Presidencia de la Comisión: Fuera del marco legal, del Estado de Derecho, no hay democracia, no hay solución a nada.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text:
Os pido honrar en el día de hoy a la resistenza italiana y a la revoluçao dos cravos, porque hay algo en lo nunca ha habido duda alguna en el socialismo europeo: siempre hemos sido y siempre seremos orgullosamente antifascistas.
@pdnetwork @psocialista
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him

text: Hoy es un día fundamental en esto: el 25 de abril se celebra la liberación nacional en Italia y Portugal. Pese a que pasaron en dos momentos distintos de la historia, el sacrificio de las mujeres y los hombres que lucharon por la libertad y la democracia fue exactamente el mismo.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Nos jugamos mucho en las próximas elecciones: nos encontramos en una lucha por el alma de la Unión Europea. Nuestros valores, nuestras sociedades, nuestro planeta y nuestro futuro están en juego.

Christian values to me does not mean putting women in the kitchen and telling them to shut up.

text:

text: Go out and vote. For yourselves, for your children, for your grandchildren. Vote for a progressive Europe.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Everywhere I go in Europe I hear young people telling me #ItsTime
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Going to vote in May in the European elections will be about choosing the kind of Europe we want to live in.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: If I am President of the European Commission I will fight to eliminate the gender pay gap in 5 years. And I will come with tough measures to tackle violence against women.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: East and West must be equal. And men and women must be equal. That is our fight in Europe.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Vaclav Havel once told me a beautiful thing: that our task is to make sure East and West are just geographical terms in Europe, not moral terms.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The cost of living in the Czech Republic is going up. But salaries are not going up on the same way. We need to work with trade unions to secure better wages for European workers.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: There can be no second rate Europeans. And citizens should have access to the same quality products all over Europe.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: I want a minimum wage in every state of the European Union. I want multinationals to pay taxes where they are making profits. Tax evasion is not acceptable in Europe.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The European Union is our home, the roof over our heads. But it needs maintenance.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We say no to governments controlling judges. Amd we stand for the freedom of the press.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Freedom needs permanent maintenance. We say no to fascism. We say no to xenophobia. We stand firm against antisemitism.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Now @CSSD is led by a generation who grew up in freedom in a united Europe. But we should never take our freedom for granted.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: In the Czech Republic, people dared to dream about Europe.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The Czech Republic is one of the places where the movements were born which made Europe whole again.

text: Spring is coming in Europe. You see that with young people in the streets fighting climate change. You see that with the #MeToo movement.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We are also a movement which does not compromise on our values. I have seen what happens in Europe when governments go back on our values and chain people to their fears.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Socialists and social democrats in government across Europe raise pensions and raise wages and protect people.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We need to let our children dream of a brighter future and more opportunities in life.

users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: If I’m President of the European Commission I will work with towns and cities across Europe to provide more affordable housing for our young people.

users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We will leave nobody behind in the green transition.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Our movement started by talking about redistribution of wealth. Now we need to talk about the distribution and protection of our limited natural resources. We need a circular economy. We need clean water. We need clean air.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We need fair taxation in Europe. Multinationals cannot make billions of profits and pay no taxes.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We need a new social contract for Europe. I pledge a strong alliance today with Europe’s trade unions. We need to guarantee decent pay for decent work.

text: All three EU institutions are ‘political’ in their own way - the Commisison, Council and Parliament. Our trademark as the @EU_Commission should be that we are ‘professional’.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: To the students marching for the climate, I say: go for it! My kids do it too and I am proud of them. I have been saying for years to young people that I love their idealism but they need to organise, so it is great to see them doing this.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: On Brexit, we have an obligation to make this divorce as amicable as possible. It is only self-defeating for us both if we make this relationship acrimonious. There is no joy in seeing the Brits suffer. It breaks my heart.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Guaranteeing the independence of the judiciary has a direct link with protecting the internal market. National judges are European judges and they oversee the application of EU law.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: A democratic mandate to govern does not absolve a government of responsibility for respecting the rule of law.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: I believe it is essential for the future of the EU that we assume collective responsibility for the rule of law. This is not just a matter for the @EU_Commission.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: You don’t address people’s anxieties about the future with numbers in a PowerPoint presentation. And you don’t solve anything by getting stuck in inter-institutional blame games.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The outcome of the next European elections will reflect the changing political landscape at national level. Every party needs to understand that in the next European Parliament, no party is an inevitable part of the majority.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The 17 UN Sustainable Development Goals would be central to the European Commission if I am it’s next President, and I would take personal responsibility for that as President.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Europe needs more social justice, with a minimum wage in every member state so that young people no longer work for a few euros an hour.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: People are now seeing the EU like a trip to the dentist. It’s important and it’s good for you, but you don’t necessarily like it. I want us to move from there to a situation where more people like it too.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: But I also see people across Europe realising that we are all in this together and need to work together. That is one of the consequences of Brexit and of the current US attitude towards Europe.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Antisemitism is the canary in the coal mine. We need to take a stand against it. There is no place for it in Europe.
